TEXT.TITLE: RUMORS THAT USSR BUYS U.S. CORN - TRADERS
TEXT.BODY: Rumors circulated among the trade this morning that the USSR may have purchased between one and two mln tonnes of U.S. corn, but there was no confirmation. One dealer said he felt some business had been done, but that the amount probably was on the low end of trade estimates. Reuter
